From: Joe Perches <joe@perches.com>
Date: Mon, 2 Mar 2015 19:54:47 -0800
Subject: [PATCH 141/177] ethernet: Use eth_<foo>_addr instead of memset
Patch-mainline: v4.1-rc1
Git-commit: c7bf716940c6a8ed39b444bfb0b97c2939ac312b
References: bsc#922833 FATE#318521

Use the built-in function instead of memset.

Signed-off-by: Joe Perches <joe@perches.com>
Acked-by: Jeff Kirsher <jeffrey.t.kirsher@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Cho, Yu-Chen <acho@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ixgbe/ixgbe_main.c |    4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ixgbe/ixgbe_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/intel/ixgbe/ixgbe_main.c
@@ -3903,7 +3903,7 @@ static void ixgbe_flush_sw_mac_table(str
 	for (i = 0; i < hw->mac.num_rar_entries; i++) {
 		adapter->mac_table[i].state |= IXGBE_MAC_STATE_MODIFIED;
 		adapter->mac_table[i].state &= ~IXGBE_MAC_STATE_IN_USE;
-		memset(adapter->mac_table[i].addr, 0, ETH_ALEN);
+		eth_zero_addr(adapter->mac_table[i].addr);
 		adapter->mac_table[i].queue = 0;
 	}
 	ixgbe_sync_mac_table(adapter);
@@ -3971,7 +3971,7 @@ int ixgbe_del_mac_filter(struct ixgbe_ad
 		    adapter->mac_table[i].queue == queue) {
 			adapter->mac_table[i].state |= IXGBE_MAC_STATE_MODIFIED;
 			adapter->mac_table[i].state &= ~IXGBE_MAC_STATE_IN_USE;
-			memset(adapter->mac_table[i].addr, 0, ETH_ALEN);
+			eth_zero_addr(adapter->mac_table[i].addr);
 			adapter->mac_table[i].queue = 0;
 			ixgbe_sync_mac_table(adapter);
 			return 0;
